        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 11:24PM CDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 1124 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southwest of Menlo, or 9 miles north of Oakley, moving east at
30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southeastern Thomas
and southwestern Sheridan Counties, including the following
locations... Halford, Angelus, and Seguin.

This includes Interstate 70 in Kansas between mile markers 63 and 74.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
